        </owl:Class><owl:Class rdf:about="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Racecourse">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">racecourse</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ur">ШЁЪҫШ§ЪҜЩҶЫ’ ЩҲШ§Щ„Ш§ ШұШіШӘЫҒ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="el">О№ПҖПҖПҢОҙПҒОҝОјОҝПӮ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Rennbahn</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ja">з«¶йҰ¬е ҙ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ga">rГЎschГәrsa</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="nl">renbaan</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="it">ippodromo</rdfs:label><rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A racecourse is an alternate term for a horse racing track, found in countries such as the United Kingdom, Australia, Hong Kong, and the United Arab Emirates.</rdfs:comment><rdfs:comment xml:lang="ur">ШұЫҢШі Ъ©ЩҲШұШі ЫҒШ§ШұШі ШұЫҢШіЩҶЪҜ Щ№ШұЫҢЪ© Ъ©Ы’ Щ„ЫҢЫ’ Ш§ЫҢЪ© Щ…ШӘШЁШ§ШҜЩ„ Ш§ШөШ·Щ„Ш§Шӯ ЫҒЫ’ШҢ Ш¬ЩҲ ШЁШұШ·Ш§ЩҶЫҢЫҒШҢ ШўШіЩ№ШұЫҢЩ„ЫҢШ§ШҢ ЫҒШ§ЩҶЪҜ Ъ©Ш§ЩҶЪҜ Ш§ЩҲШұ Щ…ШӘШӯШҜЫҒ Ш№ШұШЁ Ш§Щ…Ш§ШұШ§ШӘ Ш¬ЫҢШіЫ’ Щ…Щ…Ш§Щ„Ъ© Щ…ЫҢЪә ЩҫШ§ШҰЫҢ Ш¬Ш§ШӘЫҢ ЫҒЫ’Ы”</rdfs:comment><rdfs:comment xml:lang="el">Оҹ О№ПҖПҖПҢОҙПҒОҝОјОҝПӮ,ОөОҪОұО»О»ОұОәП„О№ОәПҢПӮ ПҢПҒОҝПӮ ОіО№Оұ П„О·ОҪ ПҖОҜПғП„Оұ ОҙО№ОөОҫОұОіПүОіО®ПӮ ОұОіПҺОҪПүОҪ ОјОөП„ОұОҫПҚ ОҜПҖПҖПүОҪ,ПғП…ОҪОұОҪП„О¬П„ОұО№ ПғОө ПҮПҺПҒОөПӮ ПҢПҖПүПӮ О· О‘ОіОіО»ОҜОұ, О‘П…ПғП„ПҒОұО»ОҜОұ, О§ОҝОҪОіОә ОҡОҝОҪОіОә ОәОұО№ П„Оұ О—ОҪПүОјОӯОҪОұ О‘ПҒОұОІО№ОәО¬ О•ОјО№ПҒО¬П„Оұ.</rdfs:comment><rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/RaceTrack"/><owl:equivalentClass rdf:resource="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q1777138"/><prov:wasDerivedFrom rdf:resource="http://mappings.dbpedia.org/index.php/OntologyClass:Racecourse"/>
        </owl:Class><owl:Class rdf:about="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Dancer">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="fr">danceur</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="en">dancer</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ur">ШұЩӮШө Ъ©ШұЩҶЫ’ ЩҲШ§Щ„Ш§</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="el">ПҮОҝПҒОөП…П„О®ПӮ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="pl">tancerz</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="de">TГӨnzer</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ja">гғҖгғігӮөгғј</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ga">damhsГіir</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="nl">danser</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="it">ballerino</rdfs:label><rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Artist"/><prov:wasDerivedFrom rdf:resource="http://mappings.dbpedia.org/index.php/OntologyClass:Dancer"/>
        </owl:Class><owl:Class rdf:about="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/IceHockeyPlayer">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="fr">joueur de hockey sur glace</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ice hockey player</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ur">ШЁШұЩҒШ§ЩҶЫҢ ЫҒШ§Ъ©ЫҢ Ъ©Ш§ Ъ©ЪҫЩ„Ш§Ъ‘ЫҢ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ko">м•„мқҙмҠӨн•ҳнӮӨ м„ мҲҳ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="el">ПҖОұОҜОәП„О·ПӮ ПҮПҢОәОөПӢ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Eishockeyspieler</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="nl">ijshockeyspeler</rdfs:label><rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/WinterSportPlayer"/><owl:equivalentClass rdf:resource="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q11774891"/><prov:wasDerivedFrom rdf:resource="http://mappings.dbpedia.org/index.php/OntologyClass:IceHockeyPlayer"/>
        </owl:Class><owl:Class rdf:about="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/PublicTransitSystem">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="es">Sistema de Transporte PГәblico</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="fr">SystГЁme de transport public</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="en">public transit system</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="ur">Ш№ЩҲШ§Щ…ЫҢ ШұШ§ЫҒШҜШ§ШұЫҢ Ъ©Ш§ ЩҶШёШ§Щ…</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="el">ОјОӯПғОұ ОјОұО¶О№ОәО®ПӮ ОјОөП„ОұПҶОҝПҒО¬ПӮ</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Г–ffentliches Personenverkehrssystem</rdfs:label><rdfs:label xml:lang="nl">openbaar vervoer systeem</rdfs:label><rdfs:comment xml:lang="fr">Un systГЁme de transport en commun est un service de transport partagГ© de passagers mis Г  la disposition du grand public. Les modes de transport public comprennent les bus, les trolleybus, les tramways et les trains, le В« transport en commun rapide В» (mГ©tro, TGV, etc.) et les ferries. Les transports publics interurbains sont dominГ©s par les compagnies aГ©riennes, les autocars et le rail intercitГ©. (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_transit).</rdfs:comment><rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A public transit system is a shared passenger transportation service which is available for use by the general public. Public transport modes include buses, trolleybuses, trams and trains, 'rapid transit' (metro/subways/undergrounds etc) and ferries. Intercity public transport is dominated by airlines, coaches, and intercity rail. (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_transit).</rdfs:comment><rdfs:comment xml:lang="ur">Ш№ЩҲШ§Щ…ЫҢ ШұШ§ЫҒШҜШ§ШұЫҢ Ъ©Ш§ ЩҶШёШ§Щ… Ш§ЫҢЪ© Щ…ШҙШӘШұЪ©ЫҒ Ш№ЩҲШ§Щ…ЫҢ ЩҶЩӮЩ„ ЩҲ ШӯЩ…Щ„ Ъ©ЫҢ ШіШұЩҲШі ЫҒЫ’ Ш¬ЩҲ Ш№Ш§Щ… Щ„ЩҲЪҜЩҲЪә Ъ©Ы’ Ш§ШіШӘШ№Щ…Ш§Щ„ Ъ©Ы’ Щ„ЫҢЫ’ ШҜШіШӘЫҢШ§ШЁ ЫҒЫ’Ы”Ш№ЩҲШ§Щ…ЫҢ ЩҶЩӮЩ„ ЩҲ ШӯЩ…Щ„ Ъ©Ы’ Ш·ШұЫҢЩӮЩҲЪә Щ…ЫҢЪә ШЁШіЫҢЪә ШҢ Щ№ШұШ§Щ„ЫҢ ШЁШіЫҢЪә ШҢ Щ№ШұШ§Щ… Ш§ЩҲШұ Щ№ШұЫҢЩҶЫҢЪә ШҢ 'ШӘЫҢШІ ШұЩҒШӘШ§ШұШұШ§ЫҒШҜШ§ШұЫҢ' (Щ…ЫҢЩ№ШұЩҲ/ШІЩ…ЫҢЩҶ ШҜЩҲШІ ШЁШұЩӮЫҢ ШұЫҢЩ„/ШІЫҢШұ ШІЩ…ЫҢЩҶ ЩҲШәЫҢШұЫҒ) Ш§ЩҲШұ ЩҒЫҢШұЫҢ ШҙШ§Щ…Щ„ ЫҒЫҢЪәЫ”</rdfs:comment><rdfs:comment xml:lang="el">ОӨОұ ОјОӯПғОұ ОјОұО¶О№ОәО®ПӮ ОјОөП„ОұПҶОҝПҒО¬ПӮ (ПғП…ОҪП„ОҝОјОҝОіПҒОұПҶОҜОұ ОңОңОң) ОөОҜОҪОұО№ П„Оұ ОҙО·ОјПҢПғО№Оұ ПғП…ОіОәОҝО№ОҪПүОҪО№ОұОәО¬ ОјОӯПғОұ, ПҖОҝП… ПҖОөПҒО№О»ОұОјОІО¬ОҪОҝП…ОҪ П„Оұ О»ОөПүПҶОҝПҒОөОҜОұ, П„Оұ П„ПҒПҢО»ОөПҠ, П„Оұ П„ПҒОұОј, П„Оұ П„ПҒОӯОҪОұ, П„Оҝ ОјОөП„ПҒПҢ, П„Оұ ПҖО»ОҝОҜОұ. ОҘПҖО¬ПҒПҮОҝП…ОҪ ОәОұО№ П„Оұ П„ОұПҮОөОҜОұ ОјОӯПғОұ ПғП…ОіОәОҝО№ОҪПүОҪОҜОұПӮ ПҖОҝП… ПҖОөПҒО№О»ОұОјОІО¬ОҪОҝП…ОҪ П„Оұ ОұОөПҒОҝПҖО»О¬ОҪОұ, П…ПҖОөПҒП„ОұПҮОөОҜОұ П„ПҒОӯОҪОұ.</rdfs:comment><rdfs:comment xml:lang="de">Ein System des Г–ffentlichen Personenverkehrs auf StraГҹe, Schiene oder Wasser.</rdfs:comment><rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Company"/><prov:wasDerivedFrom rdf:resource="http://mappings.dbpedia.org/index.php/OntologyClass:PublicTransitSystem"/>
